    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get that it can build things, but isn't the whole \"us vs them\" mentality inherent to it? even if a leader is good, the ideology itself seems to rely on excluding people who aren't part of the \"in-group.\" isn't that just fundamentally flawed in a modern, globalized world?",
