      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"us vs them\" mentality is indeed a fundamental flaw in nationalism, as it inherently creates division and alienates those outside the in-group. While it can build cohesion, this exclusionary nature often leads to conflict and instability, making it a dangerous ideology in a modern, globalized world where cooperation is essential for survival. Therefore, I view it as a net negative because its reliance on exclusion undermines the very social fabric it claims to strengthen.",
